product_name: Jouer Cosmetics Rose Gold Blush Bouquet Dual Blush Palette Mini
user_specs: ['Eye Color Brown', 'Hair color Black', 'Skin Tone Light', 'Skin Type Combination']
review_content: These blushes are really pretty and give a nice sheen to the skin without any sort of giant glitter chunks. The resulting finish is skin-like and radiant. However, be aware that these really pack a punch. Apply with a soft hand and don't put too much product on your brush; build it up!

product_name: Jouer Cosmetics Rose Gold Blush Bouquet Dual Blush Palette Mini
user_specs: ['Eye Color Blue', 'Hair color Blonde', 'Skin Tone Porcelain', 'Skin Type Combination']
review_content: I needed a new blush as my previous one had just run out and stumbled across this one. I like that it has the two options: I like to use the lighter for daytime (such as work) and the darker for when I need to go somewhere in the evenings. I really recommend this, I’ve had it for a couple months already and barely made a dent in it, and for the price you can’t go wrong.

user_specs: ['Eye Color Brown', 'Hair color Black', 'Skin Tone Medium', 'Skin Type Combination']
review_title: Lots of Product for a Mini
review_content:
I have never panned a blush in my collection... and I had resisted buying the Rose Gold full size, no matter how pretty the colors were, for this very reason. So when I saw that Jouer created this Blush Bouquet duo, I decided to give it a shot. The compact is ideal for keeping in your purse or taking for travel, and I think this "mini" has probably the equivalent amount of blush as a full size from other companies. Anything rose gold appeals to me, and I appreciate the tasteful, sturdy packaging. Jouer's formula is one of the best!

product_name: Jouer Cosmetics Rose Gold Blush Bouquet Dual Blush Palette Mini
user_specs: ['Eye Color Gray', 'Hair color Blonde', 'Skin Tone Light', 'Skin Type Combination']
review_content:
This new Jouer blush duo is a perfect combination of beautiful warm shades. The second photo on Sephora’s site makes the depth look too deep, too brown, for the left side shade. It’s actually a little bit lighter. The right side is accurate, but doesn’t show the touch of shimmer and finely milled glitter in both shades. It’s very subtle so if you’re looking for a soft glow, this will do the job. The darker shade looks great in the hollows of the cheeks, and the lighter is so pretty on the apples. They blend together nicely too. All around, a great deal!
